# CV Navale Mitratama — General Rules

## Project Identity
This is a **company profile website** for CV Navale Mitratama, a maritime maintenance company in Indonesia. The site is in **Bahasa Indonesia**. All UI copy, labels, and placeholder text must be in Indonesian.

## Tech Stack (do not deviate)
- Next.js 15 App Router
- Tailwind CSS v3 (no CSS Modules, no styled-components)
- GSAP 3.12 + ScrollTrigger for all animations
- Resend for transactional email
- React Hook Form for all forms
- TypeScript strict mode

## Design System — Non-Negotiable
Use the established design tokens. Never introduce new colors outside of:
- `navy-950, navy-900, navy-800` for dark backgrounds
- `blue-brand (#1A56A0)` as primary accent
- `blue-pale (#7AB8E0)` for light accents on dark bg
- `neutral-50/100/200/500/700/900` for grays

Use the font variables ONLY:
- `font-display` → Syne (headings, nav, CTAs)
- `font-body` → Source Sans 3 (paragraphs)
- `font-mono` → DM Mono (tags, labels, counters, numbers)

## Reuse Custom Classes
Always prefer globals.css utility classes before writing new Tailwind:
- `.container-custom` instead of `max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-10`
- `.section-pad` instead of `py-24 lg:py-32`
- `.label-tag` / `.label-tag-light` for section labels
- `.btn-primary`, `.btn-outline`, `.btn-outline-dark`, `.btn-whatsapp`
- `.service-card` for service grid items

## Component Rules
- Default to **Server Components**
- Add `'use client'` ONLY when using: hooks, GSAP, event listeners, browser APIs
- Use named exports for all components
- Use default exports only for Next.js page files

## Naming
- Components: `PascalCase.tsx`
- Pages: `app/route-name/page.tsx` (kebab-case directory)
- Utilities: `camelCase.ts`
- Aliases: always use `@/` not relative `../../`
